\section{Domain inclusion}{

Inherits the contract of \code{\link[=pull]{pull()}} for \code{survey_base}: the returned vector
includes both in-domain and out-of-domain values. \code{pull.survey_base} calls
\verb{dplyr::pull(@data, ...)} directly without filtering on the domain column,
so the combined vector mixes both kinds of rows. The user has no
per-element marker for domain membership — this is a known limitation of
\code{pull} at the per-survey verb level (not the collection layer). Use a
per-member \code{\link[=filter]{filter()}} or \code{\link[tibble:tibble]{tibble::tibble()}} before pulling if domain
filtering is required.
}

